# act config — run the GitHub Actions CI workflow locally (`just act`).
# One flag per line (# starts a comment). See docs/local-ci.md.

# Map GitHub's `ubuntu-latest` to a runner image that has the tools our
# `ci-setup` action + the DeterminateSystems nix installer expect. The medium
# catthehacker image is ~1G; the full image (`:full-latest`, ~18G) is only
# needed if a step wants a GitHub-preinstalled tool we don't (we don't — every
# stage runs through `nix develop`).
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest

# Force amd64 so runs are identical on Apple-silicon hosts (the image + nix
# binary cache are amd64). Drop this line if you want native arm64.
--container-architecture linux/amd64

# The workflow needs the NIX_GITHUB_TOKEN secret (private flake inputs). Copy
# .secrets.example → .secrets and fill it in; .secrets is gitignored.
--secret-file .secrets

# Keep the job container between runs so the in-container nix install + /nix
# store persist — without this every run reinstalls nix and cold-builds from
# scratch. Reset a wedged container with `just act-clean`.
--reuse
